\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Ross Geller -- Friends\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 Character Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Ross Geller is one of the six central characters in NBC's 
\f2\i Friends
\f1\i0  (1994--2004), portrayed by David Schwimmer. He is a paleontologist with a PhD, Monica's older brother, and the romantic anchor of the series through his decade-long on-and-off relationship with Rachel Green. He is equal parts lovable and insufferable, which is precisely what makes him work.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Personality Traits\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Intellectually insecure disguised as intellectual pride
\f1\b0  -- Ross weaponizes his academic credentials constantly, often in situations where nobody asked. It is a defense mechanism as much as a personality trait.\

\f0\b Hopeless romantic
\f1\b0  -- He has been in love with Rachel since high school and never fully gets over it at any point in the series. His romanticism is genuine, which makes his failures all the more painful and comedic.\

\f0\b Deeply neurotic
\f1\b0  -- Ross anxiety-spirals at a level that rivals any character on the show. Small problems become catastrophes in his head almost instantly.\

\f0\b Surprisingly petty
\f1\b0  -- Beneath the intellectual veneer is someone who keeps score, holds grudges, and can be quietly vindictive when he feels wronged.\

\f0\b Emotionally fragile
\f1\b0  -- Three divorces, a custody battle, and constant professional and personal setbacks leave visible marks. He is not as resilient as he pretends to be.\

\f0\b Obsessive about being right
\f1\b0  -- This is perhaps his most consistent and damaging trait. He cannot let go of being correct even when it costs him relationships, dignity, and friendships.\

\f0\b Genuinely kind underneath everything
\f1\b0  -- When the neurosis settles, Ross is a caring brother, a devoted father, and a loyal friend. The goodness is real, just frequently buried.\

\f0\b Enormous capacity for embarrassment
\f1\b0  -- Ross ends up in more humiliating situations than almost any other character, and Schwimmer's physical comedy makes every one of them land perfectly.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

